<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="M" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Mutiny1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Mutiny,</orth> subst. 1) rebellion, insurrection: <bibl n="shak. ven 1049" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 1049</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 4.142" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 IV, 142</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.1.160" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 1, 160</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.1.62" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 62</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.2.128" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 2, 128</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 1.4.77" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C I, 4, 77</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 1.3.96" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. I, 3, 96</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 3.1.126" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. III, 1, 126</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 4.1.85" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. IV, 1, 85</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 3.1.86" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. III, 1, 86</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 3.2.127" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 127</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 3.2.127" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 127</bibl> <bibl n="shak. lr 1.2.116" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. I, 2, 116</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 2.3.157" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. II, 3, 157</bibl>. Per. <bibl n="shak. oth 3.0." default="NO" valid="yes">III Prol. 29</bibl>.<lb />2) discord, strife, contention: <cit><quote>gives false alarms, suggesteth m.</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 651" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 651</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>his eye, which late this m. restrains, unto a greater uproar tempts his veins,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 426" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 426</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>with herself she is in m.</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 426" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 426</bibl></cit> <cit><quote>whom right and wrong have chose as umpire of their m.</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 1.1.170" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL I, 1, 170</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>to raise a m. betwixt yourselves,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 4.1.131" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A IV, 1, 131</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>there is a m. in's mind,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h8 3.2.120" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 III, 2, 120</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>this m. were better put in hazard,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cor 2.3.264" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. II, 3, 264</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>from ancient grudge break to new m.</quote> <bibl n="shak. rom 1.0" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. I Chor.</bibl></cit> <bibl n="shak. rom 1.0" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. I Chor.</bibl> <cit><quote>you'll make a m. among my guests,</quote> <bibl n="shak. rom 1.5.82" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 5, 82</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>